        "auto_mkdir": true,
    }
}
</code></pre> More about <code>overlay_fs_args</code> ... <p>The <code>auto_mkdir</code>-flag is necessary to create copick-directories if they do not yet exist. The <code>tmpath</code>-flag is not strictly necessary, this depends on your SMB setup (e.g. if only a specific directory is shared).</p> <pre><code>{
    "overlay_root": "smb:///shared_drive/copick_project/",
    "overlay_fs_args": {
        "host": "192.158.1.38",
        "username": "user.name",
        "password": "1234",
        "auto_mkdir": true,
    }
}
</code></pre> <p>Set up your static project</p> <p>In the case of CZ cryoET data portal datasets, setting up the static project is as easy as specifying one or multiple dataset IDs. The below example selects runs from datasets 10301 and 10302.</p> <pre><code>{
